1
00:00:11,810 --> 00:00:12,700
Don't worry.

2
00:00:13,410 --> 00:00:14,620
He won't be going to prison.

3
00:00:14,930 --> 00:00:16,380
You might.

4
00:00:20,180 --> 00:00:21,890
I don't understand.

5
00:00:21,930 --> 00:00:23,220
Zhang Chengcai

6
00:00:23,860 --> 00:00:25,250
was killed by you, wasn't he?

7
00:00:32,250 --> 00:00:33,160
At 8:50 PM,

8
00:00:33,160 --> 00:00:34,920
=Cases Between Us=
Zhang Chengcai returned to his room.

9
00:00:35,180 --> 00:00:36,959
At 9 PM, he called the front desk

10
00:00:36,960 --> 00:00:38,289
=Episode 18=
and asked for ice.

11
00:00:38,290 --> 00:00:40,250
Bring me some ice.

12
00:00:42,330 --> 00:00:43,859
The first time you delivered it,

13
00:00:43,860 --> 00:00:45,060
he was still alive.

14
00:00:47,970 --> 00:00:48,929
Mr. Zhang,

15
00:00:48,930 --> 00:00:50,250
your ice.

16
00:01:12,970 --> 00:01:14,220
To my mother.

17
00:01:23,740 --> 00:01:25,969
Zhang Chengcai drank baijiu over ice.

18
00:01:25,970 --> 00:01:28,570
An hour later, he called again.

19
00:01:28,820 --> 00:01:29,769
Hello?

20
00:01:29,770 --> 00:01:32,049
You told everyone he wanted more ice.

21
00:01:32,050 --> 00:01:34,299
But in reality, he was feeling unwell

22
00:01:34,300 --> 00:01:35,899
and needed someone to call a doctor.

23
00:01:35,900 --> 00:01:36,409
Alright,

24
00:01:36,410 --> 00:01:37,450
Mr. Zhang.

25
00:01:42,300 --> 00:01:43,620
Help me.

26
00:01:50,610 --> 00:01:52,010
Help me.

27
00:01:53,820 --> 00:01:54,980
Help me.

28
00:01:55,330 --> 00:01:56,730
You pretended everything was normal.

29
00:01:56,900 --> 00:01:58,700
When you went up
with the second bucket of ice,

30
00:01:59,020 --> 00:02:00,899
you simply stood there

31
00:02:00,900 --> 00:02:02,500
and watched him die.

32
00:02:10,180 --> 00:02:11,250
After that,

33
00:02:11,530 --> 00:02:13,300
you dragged his body into the bathtub,

34
00:02:13,460 --> 00:02:14,620
filled it with water,

35
00:02:15,050 --> 00:02:16,690
and staged a drowning.

36
00:02:18,860 --> 00:02:20,419
Chief Yuan just said

37
00:02:20,420 --> 00:02:23,489
the estimated time of death
was between 11 PM and 1 AM.

38
00:02:23,490 --> 00:02:24,930
Not 10 PM.

39
00:02:25,370 --> 00:02:27,250
And that's exactly
what made your plan so clever.

40
00:02:27,260 --> 00:02:28,419
You put Zhang Chengcai's body

41
00:02:28,420 --> 00:02:29,769
into the bathtub.

42
00:02:29,770 --> 00:02:30,579
At first glance,

43
00:02:30,580 --> 00:02:31,609
it looked like the killer

44
00:02:31,610 --> 00:02:34,459
was staging a drowning.

45
00:02:34,460 --> 00:02:35,259
As a matter of fact,

46
00:02:35,260 --> 00:02:37,139
you meant to mislead the medial examiner

47
00:02:37,140 --> 00:02:38,930
about the time of death.

48
00:02:39,460 --> 00:02:41,130
The lividity was bright red,

49
00:02:41,490 --> 00:02:43,049
patchy, and mostly across his back.

50
00:02:43,050 --> 00:02:44,130
It hadn't spread yet.

51
00:02:44,140 --> 00:02:45,699
The lividity was still developing.

52
00:02:45,700 --> 00:02:46,929
He'd been dead

53
00:02:46,930 --> 00:02:48,220
no more than two to four hours.

54
00:02:50,020 --> 00:02:51,690
You give me too much credit.

55
00:02:52,050 --> 00:02:53,410
I don't know any of that.

56
00:02:53,930 --> 00:02:55,019
Officer Yang.

57
00:02:55,020 --> 00:02:56,329
When you moved the body,

58
00:02:56,330 --> 00:02:57,609
what was the temperature?

59
00:02:57,610 --> 00:02:58,419
Freezing cold.

60
00:02:58,420 --> 00:02:59,899
Look at my fingers.

61
00:02:59,900 --> 00:03:01,180
They got so cold they turned red.

62
00:03:02,360 --> 00:03:04,089
Anyone who's stayed
at the International Hotel

63
00:03:04,090 --> 00:03:06,209
knows that the bathwater
is kept at a constant 39 degrees

64
00:03:06,210 --> 00:03:08,649
during this time of year.

65
00:03:08,650 --> 00:03:10,179
The indoor heating

66
00:03:10,180 --> 00:03:12,419
keeps the room temperature around 21

67
00:03:12,420 --> 00:03:13,769
to 23 degrees.

68
00:03:13,770 --> 00:03:14,739
Under those conditions,

69
00:03:14,740 --> 00:03:18,649
how long would it take
for a full tub of water to cool completely?

70
00:03:18,650 --> 00:03:20,209
According to Newton's Law of Cooling,

71
00:03:20,210 --> 00:03:22,979
it would normally take one to two hours
to reach room temperature.

72
00:03:22,980 --> 00:03:24,459
Could the water

73
00:03:24,460 --> 00:03:25,970
become cooler

74
00:03:25,980 --> 00:03:27,609
than the room itself?

75
00:03:27,610 --> 00:03:28,650
Not likely.

76
00:03:28,740 --> 00:03:29,780
Unless.

77
00:03:30,460 --> 00:03:31,460
Ice was added.

78
00:03:39,020 --> 00:03:42,180
Zhang Chengcai only drank
half a bottle of baijiu.

79
00:03:42,530 --> 00:03:44,300
Why would he need three buckets of ice?

80
00:03:44,810 --> 00:03:45,650
Where's the ice?

81
00:03:46,330 --> 00:03:47,620
Went into the bathtub.

82
00:03:56,370 --> 00:03:57,900
Confess now,

83
00:03:59,260 --> 00:04:00,850
and it'll count as voluntary surrender.

84
00:04:03,330 --> 00:04:04,810
I have done nothing wrong.

85
00:04:05,330 --> 00:04:06,780
Where's there to confess?

86
00:04:08,210 --> 00:04:09,130
Very good.

87
00:04:09,490 --> 00:04:12,410
You just gave up
your last chance to surrender.

88
00:04:14,020 --> 00:04:15,020
Someone.

89
00:04:27,410 --> 00:04:28,730
Let's start with the ice.

90
00:04:29,530 --> 00:04:30,969
Why did you use

91
00:04:30,970 --> 00:04:31,769
so much ice?

92
00:04:31,770 --> 00:04:33,340
- To preserve the body.
- Smart.

93
00:04:33,410 --> 00:04:35,169
That delayed the lividity

94
00:04:35,170 --> 00:04:37,520
from progressing to
the postmortem hypostasis,

95
00:04:37,520 --> 00:04:38,849
making the medical examiner believe

96
00:04:38,850 --> 00:04:40,619
Zhang Chengcai died

97
00:04:40,620 --> 00:04:42,900
between 11 PM and 1 AM.

98
00:04:43,460 --> 00:04:44,289
That

99
00:04:44,290 --> 00:04:45,729
gave you

100
00:04:45,730 --> 00:04:47,140
an alibi.

101
00:04:47,290 --> 00:04:49,209
His actual time of death

102
00:04:49,210 --> 00:04:50,329
was earlier than 11 PM.

103
00:04:50,330 --> 00:04:51,529
Shortly after

104
00:04:51,530 --> 00:04:52,650
his final phone call.

105
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:01,700
Mr. Zhao.

106
00:05:02,820 --> 00:05:05,260
I'm impressed by your imagination.

107
00:05:06,140 --> 00:05:07,220
Where's your evidence?

108
00:05:07,580 --> 00:05:08,460
We have it.

109
00:05:09,140 --> 00:05:12,580
There was a small rectangular indentation
on Zheng Chengcai's left shoulder.

110
00:05:12,620 --> 00:05:14,529
At first, we didn't know

111
00:05:14,530 --> 00:05:15,769
what had caused it.

112
00:05:15,770 --> 00:05:17,059
We didn't think much of it.

113
00:05:17,060 --> 00:05:18,410
Now it all makes sense.

114
00:05:19,060 --> 00:05:21,290
When you moved the body,

115
00:05:22,330 --> 00:05:23,820
you didn't take off your coat, did you?

116
00:05:26,060 --> 00:05:27,780
That's your badge, right?

117
00:05:43,850 --> 00:05:45,139
Stay still. Don't move.

118
00:05:45,140 --> 00:05:46,090
Don't move.

119
00:05:47,160 --> 00:05:48,769
(Manager Sun)

120
00:05:48,770 --> 00:05:50,290
It's exactly the same size.

121
00:05:50,530 --> 00:05:52,209
But

122
00:05:52,210 --> 00:05:53,699
why didn't the mark fade?

123
00:05:53,700 --> 00:05:55,019
After death, the muscles relax

124
00:05:55,020 --> 00:05:56,899
for about one to two hours.

125
00:05:56,900 --> 00:06:00,090
If a hard object presses against the body
during that time, it leaves an impression.

126
00:06:00,420 --> 00:06:01,729
Once lividity develops,

127
00:06:01,730 --> 00:06:03,460
that mark becomes difficult to disappear.

128
00:06:13,330 --> 00:06:14,289
When did you

129
00:06:14,290 --> 00:06:15,650
start suspecting me?

130
00:06:15,850 --> 00:06:16,970
Cocktail,

131
00:06:17,650 --> 00:06:18,580
Bai Lu.

132
00:06:19,620 --> 00:06:20,819
Besides Madam Zhang's room,

133
00:06:20,820 --> 00:06:23,289
the hotel's linen room
also overlooked Bai Lu's place.

134
00:06:23,290 --> 00:06:24,290
I imagine

135
00:06:24,530 --> 00:06:25,699
you often stood there

136
00:06:25,700 --> 00:06:26,769
with a pair of binoculars,

137
00:06:26,770 --> 00:06:28,410
watching the woman you loved.

138
00:06:29,330 --> 00:06:30,969
On the night Bai Lu died,

139
00:06:30,970 --> 00:06:33,340
you didn't come on duty
until three in the morning.

140
00:06:33,850 --> 00:06:35,380
Where were you before that?

141
00:06:35,850 --> 00:06:36,089
Wait.

142
00:06:36,090 --> 00:06:37,139
What do you mean?

143
00:06:37,140 --> 00:06:39,699
Did he kill Bai Lu as well?

144
00:06:39,700 --> 00:06:40,970
He didn't kill her.

145
00:06:41,330 --> 00:06:43,089
Wasn't she strangled?

146
00:06:43,090 --> 00:06:44,460
She was.

147
00:06:44,850 --> 00:06:46,460
By herself.

148
00:06:46,900 --> 00:06:48,220
She took her own life.

149
00:06:52,970 --> 00:06:55,139
The weather in Beijing has turned cold.

150
00:06:55,140 --> 00:06:57,089
Almost every household
starts burning charcoal.

151
00:06:57,090 --> 00:06:59,059
But Bai Lu's fireplace was clean.

152
00:06:59,060 --> 00:07:00,619
There were no signs of burning charcoal.

153
00:07:00,620 --> 00:07:03,259
The bed linens were neatly folded away.

154
00:07:03,260 --> 00:07:04,409
She never made the bed,

155
00:07:04,410 --> 00:07:05,089
never lit a fire,

156
00:07:05,090 --> 00:07:06,059
never tried to keep warm.

157
00:07:06,060 --> 00:07:07,090
Which means

158
00:07:07,580 --> 00:07:09,530
she never intended
to stay in that room for long.

159
00:07:10,210 --> 00:07:12,699
So it wasn't just the room

160
00:07:12,700 --> 00:07:14,460
she didn't intend to stay in,

161
00:07:16,140 --> 00:07:17,610
but this world as well.

162
00:07:28,620 --> 00:07:30,499
The ligature mark
running from top to bottom

163
00:07:30,500 --> 00:07:31,940
was left by hanging.

164
00:07:32,940 --> 00:07:33,619
I remember

165
00:07:33,620 --> 00:07:34,700
it was brown.

166
00:07:35,140 --> 00:07:36,019
But Dr. Du said

167
00:07:36,020 --> 00:07:38,059
that happened after death.

168
00:07:38,060 --> 00:07:39,769
If she hanged herself,

169
00:07:39,770 --> 00:07:42,579
shouldn't the ligature mark
have been dark purple?

170
00:07:42,580 --> 00:07:44,499
That's exactly why

171
00:07:44,500 --> 00:07:45,699
the killer

172
00:07:45,700 --> 00:07:47,059
kept making fresh wounds

173
00:07:47,060 --> 00:07:48,619
on her neck.

174
00:07:48,620 --> 00:07:49,970
To throw us off.

175
00:07:50,260 --> 00:07:52,579
The mark from the hanging
was dark purple.

176
00:07:52,580 --> 00:07:54,409
After taking her down,

177
00:07:54,410 --> 00:07:58,580
he looped a rope and a cello string
around her neck over and over,

178
00:07:59,140 --> 00:08:01,379
creating multiple marks

179
00:08:01,380 --> 00:08:02,329
to conceal

180
00:08:02,330 --> 00:08:04,410
the truth of Bai Lu's suicide.

181
00:08:09,410 --> 00:08:10,529
So it would look

182
00:08:10,530 --> 00:08:13,019
like an inexperienced killer
had botched the murder.

183
00:08:13,020 --> 00:08:14,529
You figured it all out

184
00:08:14,530 --> 00:08:15,939
from a tidy room alone?

185
00:08:15,940 --> 00:08:16,849
Not just that.

186
00:08:16,850 --> 00:08:18,209
Bai Lu was meticulous.

187
00:08:18,210 --> 00:08:19,169
She always kept every pen

188
00:08:19,170 --> 00:08:20,490
in the pen holder.

189
00:08:21,260 --> 00:08:22,610
Except one.

190
00:08:22,850 --> 00:08:25,760
Maybe she was distraught
before taking her own life

191
00:08:25,760 --> 00:08:26,819
and forgot to put it back.

192
00:08:26,820 --> 00:08:28,729
Normally, after using a pen,

193
00:08:28,730 --> 00:08:30,020
people leave it on the desk.

194
00:08:31,410 --> 00:08:33,940
That pen was weighing something down.

195
00:08:34,020 --> 00:08:34,970
That's right.

196
00:08:35,220 --> 00:08:36,250
A suicide note.

197
00:08:36,900 --> 00:08:38,010
Very likely.

198
00:08:38,620 --> 00:08:39,529
Manager Sun,

199
00:08:39,530 --> 00:08:41,169
you saw Bai Lu

200
00:08:41,170 --> 00:08:42,049
about to hang herself.

201
00:08:42,050 --> 00:08:44,370
By the time you got there, she was gone.

202
00:08:51,770 --> 00:08:53,689
You knew

203
00:08:53,690 --> 00:08:55,689
it was the Zhangs' torture
that drove her to it.

204
00:08:55,690 --> 00:08:57,049
You wanted revenge.

205
00:08:57,050 --> 00:08:58,929
So you staged the murder scene

206
00:08:58,930 --> 00:09:01,289
to make it look like
Bai Lu had been tortured,

207
00:09:01,290 --> 00:09:03,460
so the police would step in

208
00:09:03,570 --> 00:09:05,769
and expose

209
00:09:05,770 --> 00:09:07,220
their true colors.

210
00:09:43,170 --> 00:09:45,180
(Marriage is a tomb.)

211
00:09:45,500 --> 00:09:47,460
(There is no escape.)

212
00:09:48,740 --> 00:09:50,490
(Death is the only way out.)

213
00:09:50,980 --> 00:09:52,770
(Do not bury me with him.)

214
00:09:53,450 --> 00:09:55,540
(That greedy mother and son)

215
00:09:55,570 --> 00:09:57,540
(murder for profit.)

216
00:09:59,450 --> 00:10:01,370
(Justice may be delayed)

217
00:10:01,900 --> 00:10:04,540
(but never denied.)

218
00:10:18,620 --> 00:10:20,770
Your shoe size matched Zhang Chengcai's.

219
00:10:21,690 --> 00:10:23,920
You climbed in through the backyard
and up onto the balcony.

220
00:10:24,220 --> 00:10:25,379
When the footprints were found,

221
00:10:25,380 --> 00:10:27,400
everyone naturally assumed
they were Zhang Chengcai's.

222
00:10:27,930 --> 00:10:29,289
You overlooked one thing.

223
00:10:29,290 --> 00:10:30,219
Your escape route

224
00:10:30,220 --> 00:10:32,090
was impossible for Zhang Chengcai.

225
00:10:32,860 --> 00:10:33,379
That night,

226
00:10:33,380 --> 00:10:34,259
you saw Zhang Chengcai

227
00:10:34,260 --> 00:10:35,850
walk out the police department
a free man.

228
00:10:36,020 --> 00:10:37,090
You were indignant.

229
00:10:37,380 --> 00:10:39,180
So you told the bartender.

230
00:10:39,980 --> 00:10:41,259
You knew

231
00:10:41,260 --> 00:10:42,940
how he felt about Zhenzhen.

232
00:10:43,140 --> 00:10:45,340
And you knew he suspected

233
00:10:45,450 --> 00:10:47,340
the Zhangs were behind her disappearance.

234
00:10:47,930 --> 00:10:49,700
You exploited his feelings

235
00:10:49,860 --> 00:10:52,370
and led him to persuade Zhang Chengcai
to drink that way.

236
00:10:53,100 --> 00:10:54,850
Even if nothing had happened today,

237
00:10:55,380 --> 00:10:56,660
he would've ended up dead

238
00:10:56,810 --> 00:10:57,970
sooner or later.

239
00:11:24,050 --> 00:11:26,169
You turned a suicide into a murder,

240
00:11:26,170 --> 00:11:28,730
then turned a murder into an accident.

241
00:11:29,770 --> 00:11:30,970
Impressive.

242
00:11:32,410 --> 00:11:33,490
Too bad

243
00:11:34,100 --> 00:11:35,540
I made a mistake.

244
00:11:36,410 --> 00:11:39,730
You could've gone to the police
the moment you found the suicide note.

245
00:11:42,690 --> 00:11:44,130
If calling the police worked,

246
00:11:44,770 --> 00:11:46,370
why would anyone resort to murder?

247
00:11:46,530 --> 00:11:48,490
I reported Zhenzhen missing.

248
00:11:49,050 --> 00:11:50,370
Did anyone care?

249
00:11:54,650 --> 00:11:55,540
Sir,

250
00:11:55,930 --> 00:11:57,289
following the suspect's directions,

251
00:11:57,290 --> 00:11:58,689
we found a woman's body

252
00:11:58,690 --> 00:11:59,929
under a parasol tree.

253
00:11:59,930 --> 00:12:01,049
The body was badly decomposed.

254
00:12:01,050 --> 00:12:03,220
We found this beside the remains.

255
00:12:12,020 --> 00:12:13,580
It's Zhenzhen's.

256
00:12:13,650 --> 00:12:15,130
It's hers.

257
00:12:21,340 --> 00:12:22,850
It's hers.

258
00:12:28,980 --> 00:12:30,300
I made it myself.

259
00:12:31,380 --> 00:12:32,420
It's not delicate.

260
00:12:33,260 --> 00:12:34,700
When I make enough money,

261
00:12:35,100 --> 00:12:36,540
I'll buy you a real one.

262
00:12:47,170 --> 00:12:48,940
Once I become a star,

263
00:12:49,170 --> 00:12:50,370
I'll buy it myself.

264
00:12:50,570 --> 00:12:51,730
You definitely will.

265
00:12:53,380 --> 00:12:54,610
You really think I can?

266
00:12:54,650 --> 00:12:55,730
Of course.

267
00:14:24,260 --> 00:14:26,370
What is love?

268
00:14:27,260 --> 00:14:29,340
Two true hearts found each other.

269
00:14:34,930 --> 00:14:36,850
Love has always made fools of us all.

270
00:14:37,740 --> 00:14:39,490
Its sorrows have nothing
to do with romance.

271
00:14:41,620 --> 00:14:43,010
Once people fall in love,

272
00:14:44,900 --> 00:14:46,180
they're bound to make mistakes.

273
00:14:46,980 --> 00:14:49,890
If those mistakes can be excused

274
00:14:50,260 --> 00:14:51,770
at the expense of the law,

275
00:14:54,020 --> 00:14:56,220
where do we draw the line for justice?

276
00:15:02,100 --> 00:15:03,890
The test results
for the Longevity Pills are out.

277
00:15:05,800 --> 00:15:06,619
(Peking Union Medical College
Laboratory Report)

278
00:15:06,620 --> 00:15:07,739
Methamphetamine?

279
00:15:07,740 --> 00:15:09,180
Yes, methamphetamine.

280
00:15:09,410 --> 00:15:10,850
How could it be this?

281
00:15:11,260 --> 00:15:12,340
What is that?

282
00:15:13,570 --> 00:15:15,090
Something the Japanese developed.

283
00:15:15,220 --> 00:15:16,970
I saw cases involving it
when I was in Britain.

284
00:15:17,050 --> 00:15:18,449
It causes extreme excitement,

285
00:15:18,450 --> 00:15:19,850
overstimulates the nervous system,

286
00:15:20,140 --> 00:15:21,339
and wipes out fatigue.

287
00:15:21,340 --> 00:15:23,090
It's highly addictive.

288
00:15:25,020 --> 00:15:26,940
Isn't this a new kind of opium?

289
00:15:27,020 --> 00:15:28,970
If this spreads,
it could become another Opium War.

290
00:15:32,440 --> 00:15:36,680
(Jingshi Police Department)

291
00:15:40,450 --> 00:15:41,420
Move.

292
00:15:44,570 --> 00:15:45,580
Don't touch me!

293
00:15:45,690 --> 00:15:46,610
I'll sit myself.

294
00:15:54,530 --> 00:15:57,340
Where did the ingredients
for the Longevity Pills come from?

295
00:16:00,340 --> 00:16:02,010
Do you know who you've crossed?

296
00:16:03,770 --> 00:16:05,340
The money from those pills

297
00:16:05,530 --> 00:16:06,890
was never mine.

298
00:16:08,620 --> 00:16:11,499
Give us the mastermind,
and we'll recommend a lighter sentence.

299
00:16:11,500 --> 00:16:12,569
I'll be out soon anyway.

300
00:16:12,570 --> 00:16:13,730
Are you sure?

301
00:16:16,930 --> 00:16:19,339
You ruined your backer's cash cow.

302
00:16:19,340 --> 00:16:20,850
You think they'll let you live?

303
00:16:21,690 --> 00:16:23,340
You might actually survive longer

304
00:16:23,380 --> 00:16:24,770
inside the prison.

305
00:16:31,650 --> 00:16:33,420
My son's gone.

306
00:16:34,500 --> 00:16:36,770
Dead or alive,

307
00:16:37,020 --> 00:16:38,060
it makes no difference.

308
00:16:39,860 --> 00:16:42,060
Your son is buried
at Qinghe Cemetery, isn't he?

309
00:16:43,690 --> 00:16:44,660
What are you trying to do?

310
00:16:45,100 --> 00:16:46,420
As the old saying goes,

311
00:16:47,480 --> 00:16:49,160
"The dead should rest in peace
under the earth."

312
00:16:49,160 --> 00:16:49,739
Don't you dare.

313
00:16:49,740 --> 00:16:51,890
You can find out whether we would.

314
00:17:15,410 --> 00:17:16,420
If I tell you,

315
00:17:18,900 --> 00:17:20,290
what do I get?

316
00:17:21,300 --> 00:17:23,770
I guarantee you'll stay alive in prison.

317
00:17:33,820 --> 00:17:34,969
There wasn't a formula.

318
00:17:34,970 --> 00:17:36,449
Every time, I was just given

319
00:17:36,450 --> 00:17:38,100
a can of white powder.

320
00:17:38,140 --> 00:17:41,900
I'd mix it with potato starch and corn flour,
roll it into pills, and sell them.

321
00:17:42,170 --> 00:17:43,290
Where did you get it?

322
00:17:43,410 --> 00:17:44,620
Ji'an Apothecary

323
00:17:44,930 --> 00:17:46,100
at the end of the south alley

324
00:17:46,490 --> 00:17:47,530
in Xidan Market.

325
00:17:47,680 --> 00:17:55,059
(Ji'an Apothecary)

326
00:17:55,060 --> 00:17:56,140
Ma'am,

327
00:17:56,580 --> 00:17:58,700
why is Ji'an Apothecary closed so early?

328
00:17:58,860 --> 00:18:01,140
It shut down a couple of days ago.

329
00:18:01,210 --> 00:18:03,099
Business has been terrible lately.

330
00:18:03,100 --> 00:18:04,730
Might as well close up and go home.

331
00:18:05,140 --> 00:18:06,330
Shut down?

332
00:18:14,730 --> 00:18:15,999
What happened?

333
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:18,200
(End of Episode 18)

334
00:18:18,561 --> 00:18:20,201
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

335
00:18:20,201 --> 00:18:21,741
♪Troubled times
are but a laughing matter♪

336
00:18:21,741 --> 00:18:22,991
♪However, the world changes♪

337
00:18:22,991 --> 00:18:24,911
♪You'll still be by my side♪

338
00:18:24,911 --> 00:18:26,601
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

339
00:18:26,601 --> 00:18:28,171
♪Praise and blame come and go♪

340
00:18:28,171 --> 00:18:29,741
♪If this is my final chapter♪

341
00:18:29,741 --> 00:18:32,241
♪I'll solve this mystery with you♪
